reviews.text: Go here more often than I should! My friend loves their pizza slices & I prefer the calzone..call ahead & your calzone is made to order...when my sister visits, she always picks up some tiramisu before she heads back out of state. I love the mini cannollis!
Plenty of calzone selections. Sicilian style pizza is a great deal for a party. They sell regular and multi grain pizza dough.
MEATBALL PIES WITH CHEESE AFFORDABILITY AND WORLD CLASS SERVICE AND TASTE !!

Ordered a small pizza and paids for it.was told it would be about half hour. Asked where I sould wait and wastold anywhere. Sat at a table close by. Got up to  check on my after about 25 .minutes and was told I wasn't waiting in the right place. When my order  came out on time they asked me to pay again. This action was not done in a very friendly manner. I don't know if I will ever return. The pizza itself was alright

INCREDIBLE menu! Everything is absolutely delicious and there is SUCH a variety. Whether you prefer to eat healthy, vegan & wholesome, OR (if you're like me!) you prefer the yummy, sweet, fattening stuff! There is truly something for everyone. The only reason I gave 3 stars and not 5 is because the place is always EXTREMELY busy and the line always gets messed up and is SO disorganized. People end up cutting other people (whether by accident OR on purpose, either way it still stinks!). And also, the prices are above normal and a tad bit TOO high to make this place a daily routine! You'd go broke by the end of the week! BUT, if you deserve to treat yourself and have the means to do so (or if somebody else is paying the bill), then by all means, go ALL OUT at the Coffee Connection!!
Delicious coffee and pastries. Usually very busy but worth it. PS. Try the banana split coffee
So many choices! Great staff. Love this place!
This is a great place. The workers are excellent, the food is good, and the coffee is delicious. Prices are more than acceptable. Protein shakes taste amazing as well.
Coffee is great, friendly service and the breakfast selections are all pretty tasty

Trio has a great atmosphere with an awesome staff. We came in for the New Years preset menu which sounded divine! Our first courses were great, however our steak came out over cooked and we were quite bummed. Fortunately the chef came by and asked us how our experience was, and he immediately sent out a new perfectly cooked steak and won us over! The food really is incredible and the chefs do a great job. We will be back and greatly appreciate the customer service!

Though the portions seemed small, the food was very good at Trio. Our server forgot about us a few times (neglecting to bring drinks or check in about the meal), but she was very friendly and knowledgeable. Probably just overworked. The atmosphere was nice, too, though it was exceptionally loud.
Had the fish special. It was great. Grouper asparagus and potatoes. The fish was crisp on the outside and soft on the inside.

We tried this place because the chef of a restaurant in Raleigh, NC we love recommended it. The food was absolutely delicious and the hostess/host were so welcoming and kind. Unfortunately, we had a rude waiter who acted like we were inconveniencing him every time we ordered. He was very short and made a snide comment after we asked for a recommendation on an appetizer and we went for the opposite of his choice. We didn’t pick his recommendation bc he didn’t seem enthused or that he cared what we ordered. This restaurant is in my top 3 favorites while staying in Jackson; just unfortunate we had a negative encounter with a server.
Good food, reasonable price, and it's Jackson hole.
